<p>Submission rate by category monitored — assign a named owner and add to collision calendar if the checklist item touches offers across capture, email, SMS, or loyalty.</p>
<h2>FAQ deep dives</h2>
<p><strong>Reviews only on PDP?</strong> Waste — embed in browse, cart, post-purchase, winback via designed modules. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Review request when?</strong> Delivery +7 typical; +14 furniture; never pre-arrival. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Yotpo vs stack role?</strong> Yotpo captures and stores; Sequenzy/Klaviyo distribute in email. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Raw widget embed?</strong> No — fixed-ratio designed slots for mobile. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Negative reviews?</strong> CX alert — no auto-discount response email. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Supplement reviews in email?</strong> Experience language only — compliance filter. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
